2011 Yemeni protests: Rallies occur in Sana'a. (Al Jazeera) (BBC) (Press TV)Sudan's military bombs a village in Unity State, amid increasing tensions with South Sudan. (BBC)Israeli forces fire on pro-Palestinian protesters attempting to breach the Syrian-Israeli border in the Golan Heights on Naksa Day, marking the anniversary of the 1967 Six Day War; Syrian sources claim that close to 20 people are killed and over 325 injured, while Israeli officials confirm at least 12 injures. (Al-Jazeera) (The Telegraph) (Ynetnews) (The Jerusalem Post), (AP via Forbes)